Okay, anklegrabbers, listen up.<br>
<br>
Games Workshop sent Tedly Teabaggins a league pack for the Path to Glory Chaos warband rules (found in every single copy o' WD 274.)  I agreed to run it.<br>
<br>
The League seems simple, and will only last for a month.  There will be four weeks, and each week will feature a different scenario.  You can play as often as you can manage, with the caveat (The cave is at Barclay's house, if you have problems with it) that you can only play the same person once each week/scenario.  At the end will be a Mega-Battle, last man standing wins.  The winner of the Mega-Battle will supposedly get a special limited edition Chaos champion minature, yet to be sent by Games Workshop.<br>
<br>
Now, seeing as not all of us have Chaos armies, and you only need a few models in the warband (not to mention that they're random) Ted will be opening up boxed sets and selling the sprues/models as bitz.  That way you can get what you need, and this won't cost so much.  You save money, but the store still makes money!  Whatta deal!<br>
<br>
So, get yer ass to the store, pick yer favorite Chaos diety (or lack thereof, you Undivided sissy-marys) and roll up your starting warband.  The carnage starts next week!<br>
